In [19]:
def get_last_batch_index(data_path, prefix):
    filenames = os.listdir(data_path)
    matcher = re.compile(prefix+'(\d*).npy')
    indexes = [int(matcher.match(name).group(1)) for name in filenames if matcher.match(name)]
    if len(indexes) == 0:
        return -1
    else:
        return np.max(indexes)

In [21]:
n_train = x_train_3.shape[0]
batch_size = 8
n_batches = n_train // batch_size

batch_index = get_last_batch_index(DATA_PATH, 'bottleneck_features_train_') + 1
start = batch_index * batch_size
end = min((start + batch_size, n_train))
print('Starting from index {}, start={}, end={}'.format(batch_index, start, end))

while (start < n_train):
    tic = time()
    
    # Do the computing
    bottleneck_features_batch = vgg16.predict(x_train_3[start:end, ...])
    np.save(DATA_PATH + 'bottleneck_features_train_{}.npy'.format(batch_index), bottleneck_features_batch)
    
    toc = time()
    print('Processed batch {} [{}:{}] of {}.  '.format(batch_index, start, end, n_batches) + 
          'Elapsed time: {} seconds.       '.format((toc-tic)), end='\r')
    
    # Update the interval
    start = end
    end = min((start + batch_size, n_train))
    batch_index += 1

In [4]:
from keras import applications

def to_rgb(x):
    return np.concatenate([x[...,np.newaxis]]*3, axis=3)

def get_last_batch_index(data_path, prefix):
    filenames = os.listdir(data_path)
    matcher = re.compile(prefix+'(\d*).npy')
    indexes = [int(matcher.match(name).group(1)) for name in filenames if matcher.match(name)]
    if len(indexes) == 0:
        return -1
    else:
        return np.max(indexes)

x_test = du.get_test_data()
x_test_3 = to_rgb(x_test)

vgg16 = applications.VGG16(include_top=False, weights='imagenet')
